10 SECTION 3. Part 4 of Article 5 of Chapter 153A of the General Statutes is amended
11 by adding the following new sections to read:
12 "§ 153A-100. Compelled speech prohibited.
13 (a) Each county agency and department shall comply with the following:
14 (1) Refrain from soliciting or requiring an applicant for employment to endorse
15 or opine about beliefs, affiliations, ideals, or principles regarding matters of
16 contemporary political debate or social action as a condition of employment.
