22 for employment to voluntarily opine or speak regarding any matter, including matters of
23 contemporary political debate or social action.
24 (c) No application for employment shall inquire into matters prohibited as compelled
25 speech under this section.
26 (d) Nothing in this section shall be construed to:
27 (1) Prohibit discussion with or questions to an applicant regarding the content of
28 the applicant's resume, curriculum vitae, or other written work or oral remarks.
29 (2) Affect the ability of the prospective employing agency from complying with
30 applicable federal or State law, including employment oaths, appointment
31 affidavits, and licensure and certification requirements.
32 (3) Apply to speech protected by the First Amendment of the U.S. Constitution.
33 (e) A violation of this section constitutes employment discrimination.
