1 SECTION 5. This act shall not modify or supersede existing federal, State, or local
2 law governing public accommodations, as defined in 42 U.S.C. § 2000a, or private
3 establishments exempt from such requirements.
4 SECTION 6. If any section or provision of this act is declared unconstitutional or
5 invalid by the courts, it does not affect the validity of this act as a whole or any part other than
6 the part so declared to be unconstitutional or invalid.
7 SECTION 7. This act becomes effective July 1, 2025.
